ill%20help%20them%2C%20but%20not%20as%20much%20as%20before.%20They%20were%20supportive%2C%20understanding%2C%20and%20curious%20about%20how%20to%20pay%20off%20their%20debts%2C%20invest%2C%20and%20build%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ddfad439-367c-4d8a-b59a-f16aee1c71d5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%2C%20I%20give%20back%20to%20my%20family%2C%20but%20within%20my%20means%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20about%20personal%20finance%20through%20podcasts%2C%20social%20media%2C%20and%20Xavi.%20I%20quit%20my%20teaching%20job%20after%20realizing%20three%20things%3A%20I%20didn't%20enjoy%20the%20classroom%20setting%2C%20my%20earning%20potential%20was%20limited%2C%20and%20I%20was%20interested%20in%20technology%20and%20finance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20networking%20and%20months%20of%20job%20searching%2C%20I%20landed%20my%20first%20tech%20job%20in%202021.%20Two%20promotions%20and%20two%20interstate%20moves%20later%2C%20I've%20increased%20my%20income%20by%20300%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%20consistently%20save%20and%20invest%2030%25%20(and%20sometimes%20more)%20of%20my%20income%2C%20allowing%20me%20to%20afford%20everything%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20as%20a%20child%2C%20like%20travel%20and%20eat%20out.%20I%20send%20my%20mom%20money%20each%20month%20for%20her%20groceries%2C%20pay%20for%20my%20sister's%20phone%2C%20and%20pick%20up%20the%20check%20every%20time%20I'm%20out%20with%20my%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20helped%20my%20parents%20consolidate%20their%20debt%2C%20refinance%20their%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvest%20in%20a%20Roth%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20were%20able%20to%20finally%20become%20debt-free%20in%20August%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20a%20huge%20weight%20lifted%20off%20all%20our%20shoulders.%20They've%20also%20been%20able%20to%20build%20up%20their%20savings%20now%20that%20they're%20debt-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20accomplished%20so%20much%20on%20our%20money%20journeys%2C%20which%20I%20share%20openly%20with%20my%20community%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fovergenpoverty%2F%3Fhl%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22402160b9-d429-4dde-849d-3f171dcdc52d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEstablishing%20boundaries%20was%20a%20big%20part%20of%20my%20financial%20journey%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20and%20I%20haven't%20always%20been%20on%20the%20same%20page%20regarding%20money.%20They%20wanted%20me%20to%20cosign%20on%20a%20mortgage%20with%20my%20aunt%20because%20she%20didn't%20meet%20the%20income%20requirements%2C%20and%20another%20time%2C%20they%20wanted%20me%20to%20empty%20my%20emergency%20fund%20to%20lend%20money%20to%20a%20family%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20do%20so%20either%20time%20because%20it%20didn't%20align%20with%20my%20financial%20goals%2C%20and%20my%20parents%20weren't%20very%20happy%20with%20me.%20Ultimately%2C%20they%20respected%20my%20boundaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220a5e2922-cfd9-4dce-89b8-3cb4368d6e48%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20took%20me%20years%20to%20get%20to%20where%20I%20am%2C%20but%20I'm%20thankful%20that%20I%20put%20myself%20first%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20girl%20in%20an%20orange%20dress%20posing%20in%20front%20of%20trees%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a7c599aab37011780b5cd6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EViviana%20Vazquez.%3Cp%3EViviana%20Vazquez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20proud%20that%20I%20prioritized%20myself.%20Although%20I%20thought%20I%20was%20selfish%20at%20the%20time%2C%20I%20was%20making%20a%20short-term%20sacrifice%20so%20that%20I%20could%20do%20more%20and%20give%20more%20to%20my%20family%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20able%20to%20pay