r%20inflation%20and%20home%20values%20have%20climbed%20so%20much%2C%20it's%20begun%20to%20impact%20middle-income%20people%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20older%20Americans%20who%20have%20retired%20or%20are%20near%20retirement%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20tax%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomer-homeowners-cant-afford-downsize-retirement-mortgage-rates-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeterred%20them%20from%20downsizing%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20they%20fear%20it%20will%20eat%20into%20crucial%20savings.%20The%20tax%20may%20be%20discouraging%20empty%20nesters%20from%20selling%20their%20larger%20homes%20to%20growing%20families%2C%20worsening%20a%20shortage%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-outlook-there-are-no-starter-homes-for-first-time-buyers-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estarter%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20share%20of%20home%20sales%20subject%20to%20the%20tax%20has%20more%20than%20doubled%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years.%20In%202023%2C%208%25%20of%20US%20sellers%20made%20more%20than%20%24500%2C000%20in%20profit%20on%20the%20sale%20of%20their%20homes%2C%20the%20property%20data%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.corelogic.com%2Fintelligence%2Funexpected-surprise-more-homeowners-paying-capital-gains-taxes-strong-price-growth%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECoreLogic%20found%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20up%20from%201.3%25%20in%202003%20and%203%25%20in%202019.%20If%20the%20threshold%20had%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fdata%2Finflation_calculator.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadjusted%20for%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20%24250%2C000%20cutoff%20for%20individual%20home%20sellers%20in%201997%20dollars%20would%20be%20about%20twice%20as%20high%20%E2%80%94%20%24496%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20in%202024%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20know%2C%20anecdotally%2C%20is%20that%20people%20are%20feeling%20locked%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Selma%20Hepp%2C%20chief%20economist%20at%20CoreLogic%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20good%20share%20of%20people%20for%20whom%20this%20is%20the%20only%20source%20of%20wealth%20savings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2296115486-9031-4162-bf93-af81ddedccfd%5C%22%3ESome%20retirees%20are%20reluctant%20to%20sell%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Levin%2C%2071%2C%20has%20lived%20in%20Manhattan%20Beach%2C%20California%2C%20since%201978.%20Now%20retired%2C%20Levin%20and%20his%20wife%20want%20to%20sell%20their%20four-bedroom%20house%20and%20buy%20a%20smaller%20home%20in%20their%20neighborhood%20that%20they%20can%20grow%20old%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20housing%20investments%20have%20paid%20off%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20couple%20paid%20%24632%2C000%20for%20their%20home%20in%201991%20and%20it's%20now%20worth%20an%20estimated%20%242.8%20million%2C%20according%20to%20a%20local%20realtor%20Levin%20consulted.%20While%20they've%20benefited%20from%20their%20soaring%20home%20equity%2C%20selling%20at%20that%20price%20or%20higher%20would%20come%20with%20an%20extra%20large%20tax%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELevin%20estimates%20that%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20will%20have%20to%20pay%20several%20hundred%20thousand%20dollars%20in%20capital%20gains%20taxes%20when%20they%20sell%20their%20home.%20Because%20the%20couple%20is%20relying%20on%20cash%20from%20their%20home%20sale%20to%20support%20them%20through%20retirement%2C%20Levin%20doesn't%20think%20they%20can%20afford%20to%20stay%20in%20Manhattan%20Beach%20%E2%80%94%20or%20live%20anywhere%20close%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20sell%20our%20house%2C%20pay%20the%20capital%20gains%20tax%2C%20with%20what%20we're%20left%20over%20with%20we%20can't%20find%20anything%20to%20buy%20that's%20anywhere%20as%20nice%20as%20the%20home%20we're%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELevin%2C%20who%20operated%20retail%20stores%20before%20he%20retired%2C%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20a%20homemaker%2C%20both%20volunteer%20at%20their%20local%20community%20college%2C%20and%20they%20live%20on%20Levin's%20Social%20Security%20checks%20and%20retirement%20savings.%20But%20they're%20relying%20on%20their%20home%20equity%20to%20help%20support%20them%20as%20they%20age.%20%26quot%3BOur%20house%20has%20been%20a%20piggy%20bank%2C%20so%20the%20house%20is%20what%20secures%20our%20retirement%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELevin%20was%20quick%20to%20point%20out%20that%20he%20feels%20these%20are%20%26quot%3Brich%20people's%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20they're%20indicative%20of%20how%20even%20well-off%20boomers%20are%20struggling%20to%20retire%20comfortably%20in%20the%20communities%20they've%20built%20their%20lives%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20can%20you%20feel%20sorry%20for%20us%3F%20I%20mean%2C%20we%20have%20so%20much%20more%20than%20most%20people%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Levin%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20the%20circumstances%20of%20our%20lives%20make%20us%20stuck%20in%20our%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20view%20of%20beachfront%20real%20estate%20in%20Manhattan%20Beach%2C%20California.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67731e9cca1058716a5ecc90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22887%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELongtime%20resident%20David%20Levin%20says%20he%20can't%20afford%20to%20downsize%20in%20Manhattan%20Beach%2C%20California%2C%20despite%20owning%20a%20nearly%20%243%20million%20home%20there.%3Cp%3EMario%20Tama%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e76fd93a-8b42-4e2e-9c27-c69fc1b32288%5C%22%3ERelief%20may%20be%20on%20the%20horizon%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Washington%20policymakers%20are%20taking%20note%20of%20the%20strain%20on%20some%20of%20their%20constituents.%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Jimmy%20Panetta%2C%20whose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpanetta.house.gov%2Fabout%2Four-district%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edistrict%3C%2Fa%3E%20includes%20several%20pricey%20coastal%20California%20housing%20markets%2C%20has%20introduced%20a%20bill%20that%20would%20double%20the%20tax%20exclusion%20to%20%24500%2C000%20for%20individuals%20and%20%241%20million%20for%20joint-filing%20couples%20and%20index%20it%20to%20inflation.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkelly.house.gov%2Fmedia%2Fpress-releases%2Freps-kelly-panetta-reintroduce-bipartisan-legislation-make-housing-more%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMore%20Homes%20on%20the%20Market%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20designed%20to%20incentivize%20more%20homeowners%20to%20sell%20and%20boost%20the%20housing%20inventory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20firmly%20believe%20that%20such%20a%20simple%2C%20straightforward%20fix%20would%20allow%20homeowners%20to%20downsize%2C%20sell%20their%20homes%2C%20and%20secure%20their%20nest-eggs%2C%26quot%3B%20Panetta%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20also%20a%20commonsense%20way%20to%20help%20expand%20the%20housing%20market%2C%20tackle%20housing%20affordability%20issues%20in%20our%20communities%2C%20and%20better%20ensure%20that%20more%20families%20have%20access%20to%20owning%20a%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaising%20the%20threshold%20for%20the%20capital%20gains%20tax%20on%20primary%20home%20sales%20and%20indexing%20the%20tax%20for%20inflation%20would%20be%20a%20boon%20for%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20alike%2C%20Hepp%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20provide%20some%20velocity%20in%20the%20market%20and%20maybe%20release%20some%20inventory%20that's%20not%20efficiently%20utilized%2C%20like%20baby%20boomers%20living%20in%20a%20really%20large%20home%20when%20they%20would%20prefer%20a%20smaller%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20As%20of%202022%2C%20the%20real-estate%20company%20Redfin%20reported%20empty-nest%20boomers%20owned%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomers-wont-sell-homes-millennials-kids-need-housing-affordability-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwice%20as%20many%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20three%20or%20more%20bedrooms%20as%20millennials%20with%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrea%20S%2C%20a%2060-year-old%20homeowner%20in%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20neighborhood%20of%20Sherman%20Oaks%2C%20hopes%20Congress%20will%20pass%20Panetta's%20bipartisan%20bill%20before%20she%20sells%20her%20home%20to%20pay%20for%20her%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20kind%20of%20hanging%20on%20for%20that%2C%20quite%20frankly%2C%20and%20hoping%20they%20get%20it%20through%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20agent%20and%20producer%2C%20who%20requested%20partial%20anonymity%20to%20protect%20her%20privacy%2C%20bought%20her%20two-bedroom%20bungalow%20in%201994%20for%20%24245%2C000.%20The%20home%20is%20now%20worth%20about%20%241.3%20million%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Zillow%20estimate%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20She's%20weighing%20a%20slew%20of%20different%20factors%20in%20deciding%20when%20to%20downsize%2C%C2%A0including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomeowners-abandoned-by-private-insurance-turning-to-government-plans-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erising%20home%20insurance%20premiums%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20mounting%20home%20maintenance%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20gambling%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BDo%20I%20wait%20for%20that%20big%20write-off%3F%20What%20happens%20if%20they%20don't%20insure%20houses%20anymore%3F%20Is%20that%20going%20to%20make%20the%20cost%20of%20my%20house%20go%20down%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-homeowners-capital-gains-tax-home-sales-retirement-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735894801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677710e89de00e389eb43107%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-homeowners-capital-gains-tax-home-sales-retirement-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20homeowners%20who've%20seen%20their%20home%20values%20soar%20are%20concerned%20a%20federal%20capital%20gains%20tax%20on%20home%20sales%20will%20eat%20into%20their%20retirement.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-homeowners-capital-gains-tax-home-sales-retirement-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Women%2C%20Domestic%20Violence%20And%20The%20Dangerous%20Narrative%20Of%20'Misuse'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fo0genpoo_domestic-violence_625x300_03_January_25.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20ruling%20in%20%3Cem%3EX%20v.%20State%20of%20Telangana%20%26amp%3B%20Another%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20made%20some%20shocking%20remarks.%20Justices%20B.%20Nagarathna%20and%20Kotiswar%20Singh%20stated%20that%20there%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgrowing%20tendency%E2%80%9D%20for%20women%20to%20misuse%20Section%20498A%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%E2%80%94a%20provision%20designed%20to%20protect%20women%20from%20cruelty%20in%20marriage%E2%80%94by%20using%20it%20as%20a%20tool%20for%20personal%20vendetta%20against%20their%20husbands%20and%20in-laws.%20While%20the%20judges%20clarified%20that%20women%20who%20have%20suffered%20cruelty%20should%20not%20remain%20silent%2C%20their%20observations%20risk%20perpetuating%20harmful%20stereotypes%20about%20women%20misusing%20the%20legal%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20said%20case%2C%20a%20woman%20filed%20an%20FIR%20in%20February%202022%20alleging%20cruelty%20under%20Section%20498A%20and%20dowry%20harassment%20under%20the%20Dowry%20Prohibition%20Act.%20The%20accused%20included%20not%20just%20her%20husband%20but%20also%20six%20members%20of%20his%20family.%20While%20the%20High%20Court%20rejected%20the%20husband's%20plea%20to%20quash%20the%20FIR%2C%20it%20restricted%20arrests%20until%20the%20charge%20sheet%20was%20filed%2C%20as%20per%20established%20legal%20guidelines%20(%3Cem%3EArnesh%20Kumar%20v.%20State%20of%20Bihar%3C%2Fem%3E).%20However%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20quashed%20the%20FIR%20against%20the%20husband%20and%20in-laws%2C%20citing%20she%20made%20vague%20and%20unsubstantiated%20allegations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EPolice%20Efficiency%20vs%20Victim's%20Intent%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20concerning%20is%20the%20broader%20narrative%20these%20remarks%20create.%20Based%20on%20decades%20of%20experience%20working%20with%20domestic%20violence%20survivors%2C%20we%20know%20that%20vague%20and%20omnibus%20allegations%20in%20FIRs%20are%20often%20a%20reflection%20of%20police%20inefficiency%20rather%20than%20the%20victim's%20intent.%20Women%20frequently%20face%20insensitivity%20at%20police%20stations%2C%20where%20complaints%20are%20either%20dismissed%20outright%20or%20recorded%20haphazardly.%20Instead%20of%20holding%20the%20police%20accountable%20for%20poorly%20recorded%20statements%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20appears%20to%20place%20the%20burden%20on%20the%20victim%2C%20suggesting%20that%20she%20should%20ensure%20her%20complaint%20is%20detailed%20and%20precise%E2%80%94a%20near-impossible%20expectation%20in%20a%20hostile%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Court%20also%20made%20troubling%20inferences%20about%20the%20absence%20of%20earlier%20complaints%20by%20the%20victim.%20The%20justices%20noted%20that%20she%20married%20in%202015%20and%20had%20two%20children%20in%202016%20and%202017%2C%20concluding%20that%20there%20was%20likely%20no%20harassment%20during%20this%20period.%20This%20assumption%20is%20not%20only%20baseless%20but%20ignores%20the%20reality%20that%20many%20women%20delay%20filing%20complaints%20due%20to%20societal%20pressure%2C%20lack%20of%20resources%2C%20or%20repeated%20attempts%20by%20authorities%20to%20counsel%20them%20into%20%E2%80%9Csettling%E2%80%9D%20the%20matter.%20The%20absence%20of%20prior%20legal%20action%20cannot%20and%20should%20not%20be%20equated%20with%20an%20absence%20of%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judges%20highlighted%20that%20the%20victim%20%E2%80%9Cabandoned%E2%80%9D%20her%20two%20children%2C%20who%20remain%20in%20her%20husband's%20custody.%20This%20assumption%2C%20too%2C%20is%20problematic.%20Women%20often%20face%20insurmountable%20barriers%20to%20seeking%20custody%2C%20including%20financial%20constraints%2C%20lack%20of%20legal%20support%2C%20and%20societal%20stigma.%20The%20Court%20could%20have%20considered%20the%20possibility%20that%20the%20victim%20was%20denied%20access%20to%20her%20children%20or%20made%20a%20painful%20choice%20to%20prioritise%20their%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELittle%20Scrutiny%20Of%20Letter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20aspect%20of%20the%20judgment%20raises%20serious%20concerns.%20The%20Court%20referred%20to%20a%20letter%20the%20victim%20allegedly%20wrote%20to%20the%20police%20in%202021%2C%20admitting%20she%20had%20left%20her%20matrimonial%20home%20after%20a%20quarrel%20about%20chatting%20with%20another%20man%20and%20promising%20not%20to%20%E2%80%9Crepeat%20such%20acts%E2%80%9D.%20This%20letter%2C%20produced%20by%20her%20husband%2C%20was%20accepted%20at%20face%20value.%20Yet%2C%20anyone%20familiar%20with%20how%20women%20are%20pressured%20during%20%E2%80%9Ccounselling%E2%80%9D%20sessions%20at%20police%20stations%20knows%20the%20level%20of%20coercion%20they%20face.%20It%20is%20alarming%20that%20the%20Court%20did%20not%20scrutinise%20the%20circumstances%20under%20which%20this%20letter%20was%20written%2C%20especially%20in%20a%20case%20involving%20allegations%20of%20domestic%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEqually%20disquieting%20is%20the%20Court's%20dismissal%20of%20the%20dowry%20allegations.%20Despite%20the%20victim's%20claims%20of%20substantial%20dowry%20given%20at%20the%20time%20of%20marriage%2C%20the%20judges%20chose%20to%20focus%20on%20procedural%20issues%20and%20vague%20allegations%20rather%20than%20allowing%20the%20trial%20to%20proceed.%20By%20doing%20so%2C%20they%20missed%20an%20opportunity%20to%20reinforce%20the%20illegality%20of%20dowry%E2%80%94a%20deeply%20entrenched%20crime%20that%20claims%20the%20lives%20of%2018%20women%20every%20day%20in%20India%2C%20as%20per%20the%20National%20Crime%20Records%20Bureau%20(2022).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgment%20also%20framed%20the%20FIR%20as%20a%20retaliatory%20measure%2C%20filed%20after%20the%20husband%20sought%20a%20mutual%20consent%20divorce.%20This%20conclusion%20overlooks%20the%20reality%20that%20women%20often%20endure%20violence%20for%20years%20before%20taking%20legal%20action%2C%20with%20divorce%20threats%20serving%20as%20the%20final%20trigger.%20By%20framing%20her%20complaint%20as%20vengeful%2C%20the%20Court%20risks%20further%20discouraging%20women%20from%20seeking%20legal%20recourse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20most%20glaringly%2C%20the%20victim%20was%20neither%20present%20nor%20represented%20during%20the%20proceedings.%20Given%20the%20systemic%20hurdles%20women%20face%20in%20accessing%20legal%20support%2C%20the%20Court%20could%20have%20ensured%20that%20she%20had%20the%20resources%20to%20present%20her%20case.%20Instead%2C%20it%20delivered%20a%20judgment%20that%20not%20only%20undermines%20her%20claims%20but%20also%20sets%20a%20dangerous%20precedent%20for%20future%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Krishna%20Iyer%20once%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20socially%20sensitised%20judge%20is%20a%20better%20statutory%20armour%20against%20gender%20outrage%20than%20long%20clauses%20of%20a%20complex%20statute.%E2%80%9D%20Sadly%2C%20this%20case%20illustrates%20how%20far%20we%20still%20are%20from%20achieving%20such%20sensitivity%20in%20our%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20498A%20Is%20Consistently%20Undermined%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20498A%2C%20enacted%20nearly%2040%20years%20ago%2C%20remains%20an%20essential%20legal%20safeguard%20against%20domestic%20violence.%20Yet%2C%20its%20effectiveness%20is%20consistently%20undermined%20by%20narratives%20of%20misuse%2C%20despite%20overwhelming%20evidence%20of%20the%20prevalence%20of%20domestic%20violence%20in%20India.%20The%20National%20Family%20Health%20Survey%20(2019%E2%80%9320)%20found%20that%2030%25%20of%20women%20aged%2018%E2%80%9349%20had%20experienced%20physical%20violence%20since%20the%20age%20of%2015%E2%80%94a%20staggering%20figure%20that%20translates%20to%20over%20200%20million%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20growing%20trend%20of%20casual%20and%20contradictory%20statements%20made%20by%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%20regarding%20domestic%20violence%20must%20be%20addressed%20without%20delay.%20These%20remarks%20have%20a%20direct%20and%20significant%20impact%20on%20how%20both%20the%20police%20and%20judiciary%20respond%20to%20cases%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20potentially%20undermining%20efforts%20to%20protect%20victims%20and%20deliver%20justice.%20The%20judiciary%20must%20speak%20with%20greater%20compassion%20recognising%20the%20systemic%20barriers%20that%20prevent%20women%20from%20seeking%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Audrey%20D'mello%20is%20the%20Director%20of%20Majlis%2C%20and%20Flavia%20Agnes%20is%20a%20legal%20scholar%20and%20women's%20rights%20lawyer.%20Majlis%20offers%20legal%20counselling%20to%20women%20and%20children%20facing%20sexual%20and%20domestic%20violence.%20For%20help%2C%20call%2007506732641.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20authors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735894140000%2C%22visual%22%